WEBVTT

00:05.172 --> 00:07.039
SAM:
<i> Previously on</i> Aquarius...

00:07.041 --> 00:09.108
-(GLASS SHATTERING)
-Ah!

00:09.110 --> 00:09.541
You okay?

00:09.543 --> 00:12.111
You rented us this place
to scare away our neighbors?

00:12.113 --> 00:12.811
No. I did you a favor.

00:12.813 --> 00:16.248
People on your block
can't stand the idea
of a negro neighbor.

00:16.250 --> 00:17.383
Well, here's the good news.

00:17.385 --> 00:19.618
If you choose to stay,
it'll be rent-free.

00:19.620 --> 00:21.687
I'm serious about
being a great cop.

00:21.689 --> 00:23.389
'Til Priore rises
from the near-dead,

00:23.391 --> 00:25.524
I'm acting LT.
So what do you got?

00:25.526 --> 00:26.558
I think she's covering.

00:26.560 --> 00:27.426
Let me talk to him, find out.

00:27.428 --> 00:29.461
Let the detectives handle
their case, all right?

00:29.463 --> 00:31.163
You already did
your part, sweetie.

00:31.165 --> 00:32.331
Wash that out for me.

00:32.333 --> 00:33.766
All I care about is Walt.

00:33.768 --> 00:35.367
I just want to talk to my son.

00:35.369 --> 00:36.235
I don't know
where Walt went.

00:36.237 --> 00:38.337
I'm worried he might
do something crazy.

00:38.339 --> 00:39.905
SAM: Peace offering.

00:40.875 --> 00:41.974
OPAL: You know, you can stay.

00:41.976 --> 00:44.443
Aren't you expecting Cutler?

00:45.246 --> 00:47.646
Detective Hodiak, huh?

00:47.648 --> 00:48.213
I brought you something.

00:48.215 --> 00:51.316
<i> I just thought you should,</i>
<i> uh, be prepared</i>
<i> next time, you know?</i>

00:51.318 --> 00:53.252
MANSON:
You've got a choice.

00:53.254 --> 00:54.019
<i> You can be afraid.</i>

00:54.021 --> 00:58.190
<i> Or you can be the thing</i>
<i> that makes people afraid.</i>

02:11.866 --> 02:14.967
-(GUN COCKING)
-Turn around, slow...

02:15.069 --> 02:17.302
Big man.

02:17.304 --> 02:20.372
And drop me that piece
while you're at it.

02:29.517 --> 02:31.450
(CHUCKLES)

02:31.452 --> 02:32.518
Well...

02:32.520 --> 02:34.186
I guess I'll get that later.

02:34.188 --> 02:35.387
Listen, whatever it is
you want,

02:35.389 --> 02:38.757
whatever your situation,
we can solve this, you and me.

02:38.759 --> 02:40.792
Solve it? Yeah.

02:40.794 --> 02:42.828
Is this a riddle?

02:43.430 --> 02:45.430
What's your name, man?

02:45.432 --> 02:46.398
Me?

02:46.400 --> 02:48.500
Oh, I'm Jesus Christ.

02:48.502 --> 02:48.934
Son of man.

02:48.936 --> 02:51.537
Listen, this is a mistake.
You don't know who I am.

02:51.539 --> 02:54.206
Well, I know who you're not.

02:54.208 --> 02:55.874
And I'm disappointed,

02:55.876 --> 03:00.479
but I'm working with
the situation at hand, friend.

03:01.482 --> 03:03.382
Now strip.

03:05.052 --> 03:08.187
Shirt, pants. Off.

03:08.189 --> 03:09.121
Wait a minute, you...

03:09.123 --> 03:11.890
Ah, keep the volume
down while you do it.

03:11.892 --> 03:18.030
We don't wanna disturb
your creamy little piece
of cake in there, now, do we?

03:43.824 --> 03:46.491
Now, turn around.
On your knees.

03:47.795 --> 03:49.528
I'm a cop.

03:50.130 --> 03:52.264
Are you now?

03:56.670 --> 03:58.637
Think about this.

03:58.639 --> 04:04.243
What you do is gonna be
done to you 10 times over.

04:12.653 --> 04:14.419
Down, big dog.

04:14.421 --> 04:15.721
Down.

04:17.758 --> 04:20.359
(BOTH GRUNTING)

04:38.445 --> 04:40.245
MORAN: So, okay...

04:40.247 --> 04:42.014
About done.

04:42.016 --> 04:44.349
Sorry, Cut, this is, uh...

04:44.351 --> 04:47.819
Never taken a statement
like this from,
you know, one of us.

04:47.821 --> 04:48.387
It's a little, uh...

04:48.389 --> 04:50.289
CUTLER: It's not your fault
the call came in.

04:50.291 --> 04:51.356
You're just
following protocol.

04:51.358 --> 04:52.991
Let's just get it
over with, all right?

04:52.993 --> 04:56.128
Okay. Uh, brown hair,
brown eyes,

04:56.130 --> 04:58.563
shortish, greasy hair,
moccasins?

04:58.565 --> 05:00.832
I know, it's half the
so-called men in LA.

05:00.834 --> 05:04.603
I'm telling you,
he's just some
drugged-up hippie freak.

05:06.774 --> 05:09.041
So Hodiak know?

05:09.276 --> 05:11.443
Come on, Moran. Yeah.

05:11.945 --> 05:13.712
Jeanie know?

05:15.516 --> 05:17.616
Okay. Okay.

05:19.320 --> 05:20.319
So anything to add?

05:20.321 --> 05:22.688
Yeah. Keep it under your hat.

05:23.857 --> 05:25.924
(VEHICLE APPROACHING)

05:27.895 --> 05:30.062
SADIE:
You're gonna love Mother Mary.

05:30.064 --> 05:32.297
So who is she, just one of us?

05:32.299 --> 05:35.500
No. The first of us.

05:35.502 --> 05:36.702
When Charlie
got out of prison,

05:36.704 --> 05:39.171
he heard it was all love
in San Francisco,

05:39.173 --> 05:42.040
and pow,
instant thunderstorm.

05:42.042 --> 05:43.942
They were meant to meet.
She took care of him.

05:43.944 --> 05:48.246
And then when he
found me and the others,
she took care of all of us.

05:48.248 --> 05:49.448
So why isn't she with us?

05:49.450 --> 05:51.216
She has a real job. But...

05:51.218 --> 05:54.052
Now it's time to come home.

05:59.093 --> 06:01.259
(ENGINE STARTING)

06:03.630 --> 06:05.263
Jimbo, you lost weight.

06:05.265 --> 06:05.697
Small ask?

06:05.699 --> 06:08.333
Any chance it'll wipe out
what I owe you from poker?

06:08.335 --> 06:11.002
Three hundred
and sixty-six bucks?

06:11.004 --> 06:13.071
It might, actually.

06:13.073 --> 06:14.673
I'm all yours, Detective.

06:14.675 --> 06:16.842
FBI liaison.
How's that going?

06:16.844 --> 06:19.144
Oh, they're a shiny
parade of ass-clench.

06:19.146 --> 06:22.547
Who are deep in
the antiwar demonstrators.

06:22.549 --> 06:24.216
What they got you on,
follow and photo?

06:24.218 --> 06:26.918
Yeah. They're not much
for the actual work.

06:26.920 --> 06:27.219
Right.

06:27.221 --> 06:30.989
Well, I need you to get me
whatever you got before you
funnel it to them, all right?

06:30.991 --> 06:33.358
On this guy
named Robbie Arthur?
You know this guy?

06:33.360 --> 06:34.726
Oh, yeah.
A squirrelly little munchbag.

06:34.728 --> 06:37.729
Uh-huh.
I wanna know where he goes,
who he talks to,

06:37.731 --> 06:39.364
pretty much 24-7 if you can.

06:39.366 --> 06:42.167
Anything I should be
on the lookout for?

06:43.604 --> 06:45.170
(SIGHS)

06:45.172 --> 06:46.605
Him.

06:47.274 --> 06:50.108
-Isn't this...
-No questions, Jimbo.

06:50.110 --> 06:52.477
-TULLY: Sam.
-Yeah.

06:53.647 --> 06:54.813
What is this, a gag?

06:54.815 --> 06:56.681
No. Cutler's there.

06:56.950 --> 06:59.618
No doubt in
full hair and makeup.

07:07.161 --> 07:09.327
WOMAN:
No, I never heard anything.

07:09.329 --> 07:11.630
I never saw anything.
I'm sorry.

07:11.632 --> 07:14.800
But you cleaned his
dressing room every night?

07:14.902 --> 07:15.901
Every night.

07:15.903 --> 07:17.302
(SNIFFLES)
But I get to it last.

07:17.304 --> 07:21.907
It's all the way in back,
behind Miss Ball's offices.

07:21.909 --> 07:23.842
And by the time I got there...

07:23.844 --> 07:25.310
(SOBBING)

07:26.079 --> 07:28.180
Who would do that?

07:28.282 --> 07:30.982
MAN: Hey, Hodiak!
Was Raymond Novo murdered?

07:30.984 --> 07:34.519
-Is his body still inside?
-(CAMERAS CLICKING)

07:34.922 --> 07:36.655
Thank you, Francine.

07:50.704 --> 07:53.472
STAN: I'll have a prepared
statement for you in an hour.

07:53.474 --> 07:54.206
-Half hour.
-Half hour.

07:54.208 --> 07:57.242
We'll call the <i> Times</i> together,
then we'll get on the horn
with his publicist.

07:57.244 --> 07:59.845
Timmy, listen, don't leave
till we get a picture
with him, okay?

07:59.847 --> 08:01.813
SAM: Hey, hey, you gonna ask
for an autograph, too?

08:01.815 --> 08:03.615
Oh, yeah, Sam,
'cause you're so above it.

08:03.617 --> 08:05.484
You got fast as me
when the call came in.

08:05.486 --> 08:08.553
Or do you just like the girls
with the spangly pants?

08:08.555 --> 08:11.623
Ah, the business of show.

08:15.162 --> 08:17.662
Every one of
these guys crucial?

08:17.664 --> 08:18.830
CUTLER: Come on.
Guy was a star.

08:18.832 --> 08:22.267
SAM:
I'm not sure that rubs off
once you're dead.

08:23.370 --> 08:24.803
Hmm...

08:24.805 --> 08:26.571
Religious?

08:26.573 --> 08:29.407
CUTLER:
Well, funny you should ask.

08:37.251 --> 08:38.950
(WHISTLES)

08:39.553 --> 08:41.486
Someone was religious.

09:04.611 --> 09:07.646
(STUTTERS) I don't...
I don't understand.

09:07.648 --> 09:10.815
He... He's in there?
Raymond?

09:15.756 --> 09:21.026
I need to ask you
a few questions to
help with our investigation.

09:21.028 --> 09:22.260
Um...

09:22.262 --> 09:25.597
-You were the girlfriend of...
-Fiancee.

09:27.134 --> 09:30.669
I, uh, I just got
off the phone with
Mr. Novo's manager.

09:30.671 --> 09:34.806
He's on his way over.
Says he also happens
to manage you.

09:34.808 --> 09:36.107
Yes.

09:36.109 --> 09:38.810
How old are you, Miss Jens?

09:38.912 --> 09:40.545
I'm 23.

09:40.781 --> 09:43.048
And Raymond was...

09:43.417 --> 09:45.483
I... I don't know.

09:45.552 --> 09:48.153
Forty-six,
according to his studio bio,

09:48.155 --> 09:51.823
and 51, according to
his driver's license.

09:51.825 --> 09:58.163
His real name is... Was...
Esteban Novarro.

09:58.465 --> 09:59.331
Mexican.

09:59.333 --> 10:01.232
(SNIFFLES)
Yes.

10:01.234 --> 10:04.903
Can you think of anybody
that might want to harm him?

10:04.905 --> 10:06.037
No.

10:06.039 --> 10:07.806
No, never.

10:08.742 --> 10:12.277
What about the suite?
He spend a lot of time here?

10:12.279 --> 10:13.712
Whenever he was shooting here.

10:13.714 --> 10:15.480
So you must be
pretty familiar with it.

10:15.482 --> 10:17.849
Uh, no, no.
Raymond was a gentleman.

10:17.851 --> 10:19.150
Oh, no, no. I don't mean that.

10:19.152 --> 10:23.154
I just need to determine
if anything was taken, stolen.

10:23.156 --> 10:24.522
Oh.

10:24.524 --> 10:25.490
Oh, um...

10:25.492 --> 10:28.893
He, uh, he kept...
He kept watches
and things here.

10:28.895 --> 10:32.430
He had...
He had his gold watch
and his ring.

10:34.801 --> 10:36.668
The ring is gone.

10:36.737 --> 10:38.670
What kind of ring?

10:39.206 --> 10:41.039
Um, it was a...
A ruby ring.

10:41.041 --> 10:43.842
He got it when he went
to Rome with his mom.

10:43.844 --> 10:45.710
He treasured it.

10:45.712 --> 10:47.779
-This ring?
-Yeah.

10:48.382 --> 10:50.715
They killed him for a ring?

10:51.018 --> 10:53.018
I just...

11:03.764 --> 11:08.166
She's gonna be
so excited to see me,
she'll probably cry.

11:11.872 --> 11:14.239
(DOORBELL CHIMING)

11:18.545 --> 11:20.345
Hi, Mary.

11:20.347 --> 11:22.113
Sadie.

11:23.917 --> 11:25.150
Can we come in?

11:25.152 --> 11:28.920
Uh, yeah. Sure, come on in.

11:32.626 --> 11:35.360
SADIE: <i> Look at you. Pantyhose!</i>

11:35.362 --> 11:38.329
If only the squares
really knew.

11:39.099 --> 11:41.166
Charlie asked you to come?

11:41.768 --> 11:43.601
It's been months.

11:43.704 --> 11:45.837
Mary, we miss you.

11:46.440 --> 11:48.106
Does he know?

11:48.542 --> 11:51.443
Is it his? Are you sure?

11:52.713 --> 11:53.344
Yeah.

11:53.346 --> 11:56.781
Uh, he'll just be
surprised is all.

11:56.783 --> 12:01.352
He keeps saying
that he's missing you,
and now we know why.

12:01.455 --> 12:03.421
He must have sensed it.

12:03.590 --> 12:05.423
He said he missed me?

12:05.425 --> 12:06.324
SADIE: Of course.

12:06.326 --> 12:08.960
We talk about Momma
all the time.

12:09.329 --> 12:10.762
Right, Cherry?

12:11.832 --> 12:15.133
We talk about momma
all the time.

12:15.802 --> 12:17.702
Constantly, yeah.

12:19.339 --> 12:21.072
How is Charlie?

12:22.709 --> 12:24.109
He's good.

12:24.111 --> 12:27.045
But he's not the same
without you.

12:30.817 --> 12:32.217
Okay.

12:32.486 --> 12:34.285
Let me pack a bag.

12:34.654 --> 12:38.256
Oh! And Charlie said
you have some sort of,

12:38.258 --> 12:40.391
I don't know, stock bond thing

12:40.393 --> 12:44.095
and that he wants you to
bring the note from the bank
with you.

12:44.097 --> 12:45.663
He needs it.

12:46.466 --> 12:47.932
Right.

12:48.869 --> 12:51.069
Right. Okay.

12:52.172 --> 12:53.738
You're pretty.

12:55.041 --> 12:58.243
Charlie's girls
just keep getting prettier.

13:06.753 --> 13:10.054
SAM: I'm sorry, Father,
I know they're not pleasant.

13:10.056 --> 13:15.193
What I'm wondering is
do you think this is
kind of a specific message?

13:15.195 --> 13:18.029
Well, he's crucified.

13:18.632 --> 13:21.266
I... I hate to say it,
but I see

13:21.268 --> 13:23.968
things as bad as this
all the time.

13:23.970 --> 13:27.205
I'm trying to determine
if this is a deeply,

13:27.207 --> 13:28.807
explicitly Catholic thing,
you think?

13:28.809 --> 13:32.677
Or maybe just a violence thing
that happens
to look really Catholic.

13:32.679 --> 13:38.716
-If you're asking me
does it say to me...
-"Sunday school crazy"?

13:38.718 --> 13:39.250
(CHUCKLES) Yeah.

13:39.252 --> 13:42.220
Well, it's not
a very good crucifixion,
as they go.

13:42.222 --> 13:44.722
(SIGHING)
There's more to it than nails.

13:44.724 --> 13:47.425
Right. Crown of thorns.
Spear in the side.

13:47.427 --> 13:50.695
What about
the spilled wine here?
Could that mean something?

13:50.697 --> 13:52.630
PRIEST: I suppose it could.
Blood of the Christ.

13:52.632 --> 13:57.235
But, to be fair, it looks like
there's been a brawl.

13:57.237 --> 13:59.037
Yeah. Yeah.

13:59.039 --> 14:00.572
I wish I could be more help.

14:00.574 --> 14:03.942
No, Father,
eliminating theories
is helpful.

14:03.944 --> 14:06.711
-Thank you for coming in.
-Anytime.

14:08.315 --> 14:09.113
It's good to see you.

14:09.115 --> 14:12.483
-It's nice to see you.
-I wish you'd come to church.

14:12.853 --> 14:16.688
You called,
my first thought was,
you're coming back.

14:18.625 --> 14:19.891
Ah...

14:21.361 --> 14:22.660
I know.

14:23.563 --> 14:25.096
Your life.

14:25.332 --> 14:27.265
I worry about you.

14:28.869 --> 14:29.901
I'm okay, Father.

14:29.903 --> 14:33.104
I've always worried about
the path you've taken...

14:33.106 --> 14:35.373
To try and make
sense of it all.

14:35.375 --> 14:39.143
Well, it's similar in a way
to the path you took, Father.

14:39.145 --> 14:40.845
-I worry about you.
-(CHUCKLES)

14:40.847 --> 14:43.581
I knew your heart
as a boy, Samson.

14:43.583 --> 14:48.553
It was maybe
a little too brave,
a little too caring.

14:50.156 --> 14:52.156
Tough combination.

14:58.231 --> 15:00.131
Hearts don't change.

15:00.233 --> 15:02.200
Guard yours.

15:02.302 --> 15:03.868
It's a good one.

15:03.870 --> 15:05.770
Thank you, Father.

15:16.917 --> 15:19.651
You might wanna work
on that face, Charmain.

15:19.653 --> 15:21.286
Sorry. What?

15:21.288 --> 15:23.421
Poker face.
You look disgusted.

15:23.423 --> 15:25.323
Well, it's an arm
with a nail through it.

15:25.325 --> 15:27.926
And you're a policewoman,
right?

15:28.028 --> 15:29.227
Right. Thank you.

15:29.229 --> 15:32.230
What are you doing right now,
aside from hovering?

15:32.232 --> 15:34.432
Cutler has me filing.

15:35.502 --> 15:37.869
Care to dip a toe in this?

15:38.171 --> 15:38.569
Yes.

15:38.571 --> 15:42.840
So I'm beginning to think
that it looks this way
because someone

15:42.842 --> 15:45.944
was really very angry
with Raymond Novo.

15:45.946 --> 15:49.314
You mean stage a crucifixion?
Because it looks like
a crucifixion.

15:49.316 --> 15:53.117
Suffice it to say that he must
have offended someone a tad.

15:53.119 --> 15:54.919
And you want me to...

15:54.921 --> 15:55.720
Uh, double-check
cold case files.

15:55.722 --> 16:00.758
See if I've forgotten any
religious fetishistic type
murders in the past two years,

16:00.760 --> 16:02.894
as if that's possible.

16:03.063 --> 16:04.762
Look into this.

16:05.465 --> 16:06.798
It's a common nail.

16:06.800 --> 16:08.132
Oh, you're good.

16:08.134 --> 16:09.701
I didn't say it was
gonna be easy.

16:09.703 --> 16:12.303
It's an avenue.
Could lead to premeditation.

16:12.305 --> 16:15.139
We're walking it.
"We" meaning you.

16:15.475 --> 16:18.176
I know it's not as much fun
as dressing up
for Halloween...

16:18.178 --> 16:20.311
-Oh, no, I want to.
-Yeah. All right.

16:20.313 --> 16:21.813
I'll, uh,
I'll work on it right away.

16:21.815 --> 16:27.051
Whatever "it" is
better not get in the way
of filing that right away.

16:27.287 --> 16:27.719
It won't.

16:27.721 --> 16:30.321
Quit getting
her hopes up, Sam.
It's cruel, I mean...

16:30.323 --> 16:35.893
Look, you're not
the next him, sweetheart,
so I'd lose the puppy look.

16:35.895 --> 16:40.798
It's heartbreaking
to those of us
who understand real life.

16:47.507 --> 16:51.109
Lieutenant Gilbert keeps
calling from Narco
for updates, so, um...

16:51.111 --> 16:54.612
I got a lot of seeds planted.
The mafia, Straight Satans...

16:54.614 --> 16:55.546
I'm watching
the Peach Pussycat,

16:55.548 --> 16:58.416
and I'm in with some
pretty suspicious freaks
at this hippie house.

16:58.418 --> 17:01.119
And we can close in
on which of those?

17:01.121 --> 17:02.420
None... Yet.

17:02.422 --> 17:03.654
But it's all connected.

17:03.656 --> 17:04.989
You weave a tangled web.

17:04.991 --> 17:05.723
It's heroin, man.

17:05.725 --> 17:09.193
Yeah, that you're not
within a mile of, man.

17:10.096 --> 17:11.529
Look...

17:12.232 --> 17:14.832
-Supposed to be me?
-Oh, no. This...

17:14.834 --> 17:15.800
Is Mr. Druggie.

17:15.802 --> 17:19.103
Mr. Druggie wants to
import wholesale, sell retail,

17:19.105 --> 17:21.539
and live in a big house
next to Hugh Hefner.

17:21.541 --> 17:23.608
-Now, you see this leg?
-Mm-hmm.

17:23.610 --> 17:24.642
That is Gladner.

17:24.644 --> 17:28.179
-Oh.
-Gladner. Well,
he's dead, right?

17:29.082 --> 17:30.081
Bye, leg.

17:30.083 --> 17:32.183
I'm gonna take out Marvin.

17:32.719 --> 17:35.453
Lucille, Vickery and Roy.

17:35.455 --> 17:37.321
Gee, who told you I like it
when there's pictures?

17:37.323 --> 17:42.393
But take away all those cats,
and Mr. Druggie's
still going strong.

17:42.395 --> 17:43.861
Until...

17:47.567 --> 17:49.133
Guapo.

17:50.036 --> 17:51.369
That's what I'm working at.

17:51.371 --> 17:52.537
Well, thanks for that.

17:52.539 --> 17:57.108
I feel I understand crime
a lot better now.

17:57.110 --> 17:58.543
